0391.Lore worth learning, learn flawlessly Live by that learning thoroughly.
0392.Letter, number, art and science Of living kind both are the eyes.
0393.The learned alone have eyes on face The ignorant two sores of disgrace.
0394.To meet with joy and part with thought Of learned men this is the art.
0395.Like poor before rich they yearn: For knowledge: the low never learn.
0396.As deep you dig the sand spring flows As deep you learn the knowledge grows.
0397.All lands and towns are learner's own Why not till death learning go on!
0398.The joy of learning in one birth Exalts man upto his seventh.
0399. The learned foster learning more On seeing the world enjoy their lore.
